node.text: For those of you who have been following me for a while know I’ve struggled with melasma, aka hyperpigmentation. My melasma began during pregnancy and got worse while breastfeeding. Some things that were making my melasma worse were hot yoga and sunlight- two things I was not willing to give up. So when I heard that one of my favorite skincare brands had created a supplement to combat melasma, I had to give it a try. BLUR POTION is an antioxidant-rich blend of skin-reviving nutrients and plant extracts proven to fade and blur all forms of hyperpigmentation and UV damage—including melasma, sun spots and post-zit dark spots—from the inside out. As you can see, it worked for me! Totally recommend :) Use AURORA for 15% off! @zitsticka #zitsticka #zittycommittee

node.text:
Okay so making a drastic pivot from my last tear jerker post, but I had to share with you my most recent obsession: meet @thecobaboard . This has been a godsent for getting back into shape after having Solei. They call it a glute trainer but it actually works all the muscles with a variety of resistance bands. One of the things I noticed after both babies is that my joints and ligaments are more fragile and so low impact toning is the absolute most effective way to get results without causing injury. Not being able to go to my workout classes has sucked but this board can go anywhere with me (super light) and it’s extremely affordable compared to other at home devices. Their website is also so user friendly and packed with tons of workouts. I’ll be giving everyone in my family this for Christmas (sorry to spoil the surprise family). They’re having a holiday sale and I got you an extra $40 off wirh code AURORA. You’re welcome 😘 #cobastrong 

(See stories for swipe up)

node.text:
One of the most important routines I had during both my pregnancies was consistent workout. Pregnancy can often feel like a rollercoaster of hormones and a loss of control over your own body. Getting my blood flowing, releasing endorphins and building strength in preparation for delivery helped me regain a sense of control over my fluctuating hormones and changing body. 

Making an effort to keep my muscles strong and get my heart rate up several days a week helped me keep in tune with my nutritional and physical needs, as well as my baby’s (which I believe helped save my baby’s life). Body awareness is crucial during pregnancy, as your balance shifts, blood volume nearly doubles and breathing becomes more difficult. 

Many women worry about continuing their exercise routines throughout pregnancy. I admit, after several miscarriages, I was terrified of overdoing it when I became pregnant with Remi. I did my research and talked to my doctor and checked in with my body. I found that not working out was actually more dangerous than continuing a moderate routine. Of course not all exercise is safe, but generally speaking, there is no reason to avoid exercise if your doctor gives you clearance. 

Some things to avoid during pregnancy include excessive heat, lifting and twisting with compression. It’s important to stay hydrated and get plenty of rest to help avoid overexertion. Also be careful not to overstretch, as your body releases hormones that make you more flexible than usual and therefore more susceptible to injury. 

Check out my stories for more details on these specific exercises with @purebodyballistics !

node.text:
I love these gummies because they are so simple to make and super healthy.
Recipe:
*fruit juice...fresh squeezed is ideal. We use watermelon juice here.
*Unflavored Gelatin... @vitalproteins is amazing because it comes from pasture-raised, grass- fed bovine hide. .
*Sweetener... agave, honey, maple syrup are good options. Sometimes I skip the sweetener all together if I use a naturally very sweet juice.

FYI:
Gelatin makes up almost 1/3 the protein in our bodies and affects everything from our joints to our immune system, hair and nails. While I generally encourage a plant based diet, consuming gelatin is much more environmentally-friendly than lean meat because it uses parts of the animal that would otherwise be discarded, helping to reduce food waste and showing reverence for the life that was given.

Special thanks to @christinebullock and Remi x 2 🥰

node.text:
Watch my friend @christinebullock make her famous Valentine’s Day Chocolate 🍫and watch me be sous chef/ eat all the ingredients throughout the process 👩🏼‍🍳 ..... Recipe:
• 60g cacao butter, chopped into small chunks
• 1/3 cup raw cacao powder
• 2 tbsp raw organic coconut oil • 2 tbsp tahini or macadamia nut butter
• 1-2 tbsp raw honey
• 1/4 tsp vanilla extract
• Optional toppings: orange zest, dried cherries, candied ginger

Directions:
1. Melt cacao butter in a glass bowl over boiling water.
2. Stir in all other ingredients and remove from heat.
3. Pour chocolate into molds or a flat tray lined with parchment paper. Place in freezer.
4. It takes 10-20 minutes to set. Either pop the molds out or break the brick of chocolate into pieces.
5. Store in an airtight container in the refrigerator or freezer.

node.text: For those of you who have been following me for a while know I’ve struggled with melasma, aka hyperpigmentation. My melasma began during pregnancy and got worse while breastfeeding. Some things that were making my melasma worse were hot yoga and sunlight- two things I was not willing to give up. So when I heard that one of my favorite skincare brands had created a supplement to combat melasma, I had to give it a try. As you can see, it worked for me! Totally recommend :) Use AURORA for 15% off! @zitsticka #zitsticka #zittycommittee

node.text:
The recent news about the child graves found at the Canadian Residential Schools has lead me down a rabbit hole of investigation and my heart is heavy. Today I wear orange on Canada’s National Indigenous Peoples Day to show support toward the First Nations People and to remember the attempted genocide by the colonists, government and church. This is very recent history and is grossly underreported, so here I am, debby downer, spreading the word and dampening your feed with sad content. It is the very least we can do to spread awareness so that history doesn’t keep repeating itself in this awful way. The horrors of forced cultural assimilation are not unique to Canada and are not an “olden days” problem. Thinking of the survivors and remembering all children and families torn apart. #nationalindigenouspeoplesday 
#firstnations #indigenouspeoplesday #canadianresidentialschools

node.text: And just like that, remi is 3 years old. Not a day has gone by since you made me a mommy that you havn’t blow me away with your bright, precocious personality. It is absolutely terrifying to love something so much but I wouldnt change a thing. Actually naps. I would love if you would nap again. Please for the love of god, nap.

node.text:
You guys know I like to run an honest page over here and I’ll always be real about what I’m doing to look and feel my best. I’m not going to waste your time talking about spf and exercise. You know those tricks so I’m gonna shoot you straight. Go to @protorc.wellness . Knock 3 times. Ask for Anya. Tell her Aurora sent you if you want 25% off. I’ve tried the Morpheus8 and Evoke treatments and Ive noticed a difference in skin tightening, tone and texture (like my muse in slide #2). Aging gracefully doesn't mean you have to wear your stretch marks and sagging skin with pride (but if you want to, more power to you!!). You should feel proud to do whatever is necessary to stride into your older years with confidence and for me that means noninvasive treatments that help the body build back its own collagen and elastin. Nothing’s free in this world, but I got u 25% off and their prices are the lowest I’ve seen even before the discount. You’re welcome :) Feel free to message me or @protorc.wellness with any questions! 
#evoke #morpheus8

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Aurora Culpo on June 06, 2021 tagging @potterybarn, @luluandgeorgia, @lulusimonstudio, @rhgallerie, and @lettucegrow. May be an image of 2 people, child, people standing and indoor.

node.text:
I added some new details to the house that I wanted to share!
1. Window treatments* They are subtle but bring so much warmth. I went with @everhem Roman shades again and was so happy how they turned out (especially in the bathroom they add another layer of sexy).
2. Framed photos* Still loving my @framebridge grid wall but I added another small gallery of photos I got online and edited to be kind of vintagey/sepia. 
3. Lighting* I swapped out the chandelier for one i like better and happens to also be like 10x cheaper than the previous Serena and lily one i had up. The new one is from @luluandgeorgia and was a few hundred$ rather than a few thousand$. Yes plz.
4. Art* The painting is @potterybarn and it’s perfect for the room but overpriced for a print.  I thought it would be paint and was disappointed by the lack of real texture.
That’s all for now!
Ps. I went full on Martha Stewart mode and made outdoor pendant lights. Think hot glue gun, rope, shells, fringe. My mom said “wow! They’re so....homemade!” 😂 so you can imagine how awful they are. Who wants to see??
